        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 14 at 11:07AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>A band of heavier snowfall is moving northward through the
Whitehall, Elk Park and Boulder areas as of 11 AM this morning.
This also includes portions of Interstate 15 over Elk Park Pass
from Butte to Boulder and portions of Interstate 90 over Homestake
Pass from Butte to Cardwell Hill.

Visibility will fall down to a quarter of a mile for a short time.
Roadways will become snow covered and slippery. New snow
accumulations of around a half inch are possible as this band of
snow moves through.
</description>
